Hi. I think I have my FV version of Ferret (module for ferroic systems) working. Some of the FV kernels are elemental, some are flux kernels. It seems to me that when evaluating the residuals for elemental kernels, I can either evaluate variables/functors on quadrature points and would as an example have the residual as
    return prefactor * (_mag_y[_qp]* _nz[_qp] - _mag_z[_qp]* _ny[_qp]);

where _mag_x, _nx etc are functors and prefactor is ADReal,
or I can define elemental values like
  ADReal _mag_x_elem = _mag_x(makeElemArg(_current_elem),determineState());
  ADReal _mag_y_elem = _mag_y(makeElemArg(_current_elem),determineState());

and similarly for _ny_elem and _ny_elem and evaluate the residual as
 return  prefactor * (_mag_z_elem * _nx_elem - _mag_x_elem * _nz_elem);

Am I correct that either one works, and, if so, is there any particular advantage to one vs the other?

